x4freetext: Neutron yield from thick C-13 target at E(p)=30 MeV.
Neutron yields are compared with a Monte-Carlo
based model prediction and with the experimental
neutron yield of proton and deuteron beams impinging
on natural carbon thick targets.
K-130 accelerator.
*By authors*. TOF values are indeed experimental, but
activation tabulated values are parameters used to
reproduce the set of overlap integrals of activation
cross-section and double-differential spectrum.
The neutron spectrum is obtained by interpolation in
these tables. The integral of the spectrum is well
defined, but the individual values are unstable due to
the flat chi-square surface.
Therefore giving errors on the spectrum is quite
arbitrary.
The data were received from G.Lhersonneau.
By SB
SD: Small correction in REFERENCE
(D..Vakhtin -> D.Vakhtin). Two refs moved to REL-REF.
Carbon target, consisted of graphite pills, diameter
24-mm, height 16-mm, enriched to 82% in C-13,
resulting in a density 0.67 g/cm**3, were used for the
measurements at 20 and 25 MeV. For the measurement at
40 MeV an extra thickness of 1.1 g/cm**2 in powder form
was added on the beam-facing side of the block in order
to increase the length above the proton range (about
1.8-g/m**2). The powder was confined by inserting a
0.5-mm thick Al disk so that the actual beam energy on
the target was lowered to 38.5 MeV.
Four position sensitive neutron detectors(PSND)
A PSND module is a 1 m long, 6 cm diameter quartz tube
filled with Ne-213 liquid scintillator.

x4freetext: The activities induced by the neutron flux were
counted off-line during up to 1 month after
irradiation.
During irradiation of the C-13 target foils of Al,
Co, Ni, In and Bi, each of 1-mm thickness and
25*25-mm**2 area, were placed at 14 cm(E(p)=20 and
25 MeV) and 28 cm(E(p)=40 MeV) from the target center.
Corrections for finite foil area and thickness were
made.
.Gamma-spectroscopic techniques.
*By authors*.After normalization for number of target
nuclei per unit surface, solid angle of the foil viewed
from the target and particle beam current one obtains a
at each angle a set of experimental values of overlap
integrals.
